com.sap.sxe.db

Class db

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sap.sxe.db.db

  • public class db
extends java.lang.Object
    The db class holds a set of db objects, for each set of connection parameter, one db object. Multiple clients can use one db object which holds a physical database connection. This connection is closed only if the db object is not used by any clients anymore.

      • db_start_trans

        public void db_start_trans()
                    throws exc_database_error
        Starts a transaction IF currently not in transaction If the transaction is started it can be terminated with db_commit or db_rollback. If currently a transaction is running, this command will be IGNORED
        Throws:
        exc_database_error

      • db_commit

        public void db_commit()
               throws exc_database_error
        Commit makes all changes made since the previous commit/rollback permanent and releases any database locks currently held by the Connection. This method should only be used when auto commit has been disabled. See java.sql.Connection.
        Throws:
        exc_database_error

      • db_rollback

        public void db_rollback()
                 throws exc_database_error
        Rollback drops all changes made since the previous commit/rollback and releases any database locks currently held by the Connection. This method should only be used when auto commit has been disabled. See java.sql.Connection.
        Throws:
        exc_database_error
